The Rector of Sandringham has the responsibility for eight parishes and six churches in addition to being one of The Queen's Chaplains. Despite this, The Church is alive, and there are services in all the churches on most Sundays and Feast Days.
The Rector can often be seen striding through the villages in his Norfolk jacket and cap on his weekly visits to the sick and infirm.
In addition to the usual Sunday services, there is a flourishing Childrens' Church and the Group Council arranges Lent discussion groups and visits to Diocesan services in Norwich Cathedral. {This section has been researched and {written by S.M.Pocklington and the {children of West Newton V.A.P.School.}
